name: DOOM WOOD
description:
Limited Edition (of 25) Holiday 2012 collaboration between Corpse Corps Boards of NYC and Radlands Clothing of Philadelphia.

Both companies share a love for primitive skateboarding and all things heavy, so the collaboration was a natural joining of camps, the brotherhood network extended. DOOM WOOD is a coffin shaped board reminiscent of 80's pool shapes and feature's the artwork of artist Matt Gribben (Radlands/Traffic) and Jordan Walzack (Corpse Corps).

Coffin shaped 7-ply American Maple deck produced here on the East Coast utilizing the same wood distributors that supplied such influential board companies as Blockhead Skateboards (c.1990), Concrete Jungle (c.1987), and JFA (c.1985).

32.25 x 9.25-inch fully functional coffin deck.

Dual kicktails
